10
00:02:27.410 --> 00:02:29.810
No. no. no. No. please!

11
00:02:29.910 --> 00:02:34.180
[screaming]

12
00:02:35.420 --> 00:02:36.650
[groaning]

13
00:02:36.750 --> 00:02:39.310
Fuck you. Prince Drahar!

14
00:02:39.420 --> 00:02:42.860
Fuck your whore mother

15
00:02:39.420 --> 00:02:42.860
and bastard father!

16
00:02:42.960 --> 00:02:44.590
[grunts]

17
00:02:45.330 --> 00:02:47.960
[groaning] No. no! No!

18
00:02:48.030 --> 00:02:50.160
[groaning]

19
00:02:51.600 --> 00:02:52.590
[screams]

20
00:02:55.940 --> 00:02:58.130
[grunting]

21
00:02:58.210 --> 00:03:00.610
[whistling in distance]

22
00:03:04.810 --> 00:03:06.710
[indistinct shouting]

23
00:03:08.050 --> 00:03:10.680
[roars]

24
00:03:12.150 --> 00:03:13.380
[man] Dragon!

25
00:03:13.490 --> 00:03:16.690
Hail Prince Daemon! [laughs]

26
00:03:17.730 --> 00:03:19.060
[Caraxes whinnies]

27
00:03:19.160 --> 00:03:22.330
Burn the fucking Triarchy cunts alive!

28
00:03:23.570 --> 00:03:27.970
[people screaming]

29
00:03:30.040 --> 00:03:31.470
Here. my Prince.

30
00:03:32.640 --> 00:03:34.370
Save me!

31
00:03:34.480 --> 00:03:35.470
[screams]

32
00:03:39.350 --> 00:03:41.840
- [roars]

33
00:03:39.350 --> 00:03:41.840
- [people screaming]

34
00:03:42.980 --> 00:03:44.420
[man 1] To the caves! Now!

35
00:03:44.520 --> 00:03:47.510
[indistinct shouting]

36
00:03:47.590 --> 00:03:49.490
[man 2 screaming]

37
00:03:52.590 --> 00:03:54.320
[man 3] Retreat to the caves!

38
00:03:54.400 --> 00:03:55.730
[indistinct shouting]

39
00:03:56.400 --> 00:03:58.870
[Caraxes roars]

40
00:04:04.240 --> 00:04:05.610
[man screaming]

41
00:04:12.950 --> 00:04:14.880
[Caraxes growls]

42
00:04:15.450 --> 00:04:17.110
[whinnies]

43
00:04:17.220 --> 00:04:18.590
[Prince Daemon] Where are you?

44
00:04:21.020 --> 00:04:23.220
Come out and face me. Drahar!

45
00:04:25.290 --> 00:04:27.560
- Come out. Drahar!

46
00:04:25.290 --> 00:04:27.560
- [Caraxes growls]

47
00:04:28.060 --> 00:04:29.760
[Prince Daemon] Where are you?

48
00:04:30.800 --> 00:04:33.290
I'm gonna feed you to your own crabs!

49
00:04:34.100 --> 00:04:35.590
Where are you?

50
00:04:35.700 --> 00:04:37.800
[sinister music playing]

51
00:04:43.910 --> 00:04:45.380
[Caraxes whinnies]

52
00:04:47.380 --> 00:04:48.750
[snarls]

53
00:04:51.220 --> 00:04:53.780
[shrieking]

54
00:05:11.410 --> 00:05:13.570
[Aegon Il babbling]

55
00:05:13.640 --> 00:05:15.110
[man 1] He has your hair. Your Grace.

56
00:05:16.340 --> 00:05:17.840
[Viserys I] He does have my hair.

57
00:05:17.950 --> 00:05:20.420
- [man 2] He has your eyes. Your Grace.

58
00:05:17.950 --> 00:05:20.420
- Yes. he does.

59
00:05:20.480 --> 00:05:22.420
[all laughing]

60
00:05:22.480 --> 00:05:23.920
[Viserys I] And you have my nose.

61
00:05:22.480 --> 00:05:23.920
don't you?

62
00:05:23.990 --> 00:05:28.150
Two years old and already our boy

63
00:05:23.990 --> 00:05:28.150
has a kingly presence.

64
00:05:28.660 --> 00:05:31.490
He may yet. brother.

65
00:05:28.660 --> 00:05:31.490
but this morning he insisted on eating

66
00:05:31.590 --> 00:05:33.290
porridge with his hands.

67
00:05:33.500 --> 00:05:34.830
[laughs]

68
00:05:34.930 --> 00:05:36.190
He will grow.

69
00:05:37.530 --> 00:05:40.370
We're quite a party

70
00:05:37.530 --> 00:05:40.370
assembled in his honor.

71
00:05:41.340 --> 00:05:44.800
And surely by the end of this hunt.

72
00:05:41.340 --> 00:05:44.800
we shall have more to celebrate.

73
00:05:44.870 --> 00:05:47.000
And what is that. pray tell.

74
00:05:47.110 --> 00:05:49.270
It is Aegon's second name day.

75
00:05:49.340 --> 00:05:50.780
His infancy's behind him.

76
00:05:51.280 --> 00:05:53.870
It only remains for Viserys to name him

77
00:05:51.280 --> 00:05:53.870
heir to the throne.

78
00:05:53.980 --> 00:05:56.210
I wouldn't be so sure.

79
00:05:56.320 --> 00:05:57.810
He's the King's firstborn son.

80
00:05:57.890 --> 00:06:00.790
I don't know that His Grace

81
00:05:57.890 --> 00:06:00.790
sees it so clearly.

82
00:06:02.460 --> 00:06:05.050
Then it lies with you

83
00:06:02.460 --> 00:06:05.050
to make him see it...

84
00:06:05.830 --> 00:06:07.660
Lord Hand.

85
00:06:07.730 --> 00:06:09.160
[Tyland] Your Grace...

86
00:06:11.070 --> 00:06:13.300
I bring urgent news from the Stepstones.

87
00:06:13.970 --> 00:06:16.300
The Crabfeeder has dug in

88
00:06:13.970 --> 00:06:16.300
for siege on Bloodstone

89
00:06:16.370 --> 00:06:18.840
while his men sabotage our fleet

90
00:06:16.370 --> 00:06:18.840
under the cover of dark.

91
00:06:18.910 --> 00:06:20.310
- Not today. Tyland.

92
00:06:18.910 --> 00:06:20.310
- [shrieks]

93
00:06:20.380 --> 00:06:23.500
The matter of the Stepstones

94
00:06:20.380 --> 00:06:23.500
is regrettably urgent.

95
00:06:23.580 --> 00:06:25.310
It's been three years.

96
00:06:25.380 --> 00:06:27.650
- It can wait another three days.

97
00:06:25.380 --> 00:06:27.650
- [babbling]

98
00:06:31.820 --> 00:06:33.880
[Viserys I] Come. eat.

99
00:06:33.990 --> 00:06:36.220
Fortify yourselves for the journey.

100
00:06:37.390 --> 00:06:38.520
Please.

101
00:06:39.230 --> 00:06:40.590
Is the baggage train ready?

102
00:06:40.700 --> 00:06:42.820
It is presently massing

103
00:06:40.700 --> 00:06:42.820
at the River Gate.

104
00:06:42.900 --> 00:06:45.660
Lord Jason expects us

105
00:06:42.900 --> 00:06:45.660
in the Kingswood before midday.

106
00:06:45.730 --> 00:06:49.030
- Have you seen Rhaenyra?

107
00:06:45.730 --> 00:06:49.030
- I have not. Your Grace.

108
00:06:51.110 --> 00:06:54.410
With the Triarchy now sheltering

109
00:06:51.110 --> 00:06:54.410
in Bloodstone's caves.

110
00:06:54.510 --> 00:06:56.910
the threat of the dragons is blunted.

111
00:06:57.010 --> 00:06:59.040
They don't have foot soldiers.

112
00:06:59.110 --> 00:07:02.520
But their sellswords have been

113
00:06:59.110 --> 00:07:02.520
withdrawing in droves. Your Grace.

114
00:07:02.580 --> 00:07:05.780
Even the mercenaries can see

115
00:07:02.580 --> 00:07:05.780
that it is a losing effort.

116
00:07:05.890 --> 00:07:06.950
Where's Rhaenyra?

117
00:07:07.520 --> 00:07:09.120
I cannot be sure at present. Your Grace.

118
00:07:09.220 --> 00:07:12.290
The Velaryon forces have suffered

119
00:07:09.220 --> 00:07:12.290
heavy attrition. Your Grace.

120
00:07:13.190 --> 00:07:15.890
The seeds of dissent are sown

121
00:07:13.190 --> 00:07:15.890
amongst the rank and file.

122
00:07:16.630 --> 00:07:18.690
Daemon has driven the men hard.

123
00:07:18.770 --> 00:07:21.240
They have begun to question his command.

124
00:07:22.240 --> 00:07:24.800
If the Crown were ever to intervene...

125
00:07:24.910 --> 00:07:26.070
- Tyland--

126
00:07:24.910 --> 00:07:26.070
- ...now is the time.

127
00:07:26.140 --> 00:07:28.470
Daemon and the Sea Snake

128
00:07:26.140 --> 00:07:28.470
started their war

129
00:07:28.580 --> 00:07:30.600
without His Grace's leave.

130
00:07:30.710 --> 00:07:33.410
Were he to intervene now after so long.

131
00:07:33.480 --> 00:07:35.310
it would make the Crown appear weak.

132
00:07:35.420 --> 00:07:36.910
Can someone tell me

133
00:07:36.990 --> 00:07:39.920
where in the seven hells

134
00:07:36.990 --> 00:07:39.920
Rhaenyra might be?

135
00:07:39.990 --> 00:07:45.090
[singing] Under the dragon's eye

136
00:07:46.230 --> 00:07:51.390
Under the dragon's eye

137
00:07:51.930 --> 00:07:52.990
Again.

138
00:07:53.100 --> 00:07:54.300
[birds chirping]

139
00:07:54.400 --> 00:07:56.600
Perhaps the Princess

140
00:07:54.400 --> 00:07:56.600
might like to hear something else?

141
00:07:56.670 --> 00:07:58.500
She would not. Play it again.

142
00:08:02.510 --> 00:08:03.410
[Samwell clears throat]

143
00:08:03.480 --> 00:08:04.470
[playing mandolin]

144
00:08:04.580 --> 00:08:07.610
[singing] She fled with her ships

145
00:08:07.680 --> 00:08:10.520
And her people

146
00:08:10.620 --> 00:08:13.780
Her heart broken for those...

147
00:08:14.790 --> 00:08:16.120
Your Grace.

148
00:08:16.190 --> 00:08:17.590
Did I say to stop?

149
00:08:21.960 --> 00:08:24.160
[clicks tongue] From the beginning.

150
00:08:25.330 --> 00:08:26.600
[Samwell clears throat]

151
00:08:28.840 --> 00:08:29.700
[playing mandolin]

152
00:08:29.800 --> 00:08:32.800
She fled with her ships

153
00:08:32.870 --> 00:08:35.810
- [Alicent] Rhaenyra?

154
00:08:32.870 --> 00:08:35.810
- Yes. my queen?

155
00:08:36.510 --> 00:08:38.810
Your presence is wanted

156
00:08:36.510 --> 00:08:38.810
in the outer courtyard.

157
00:08:38.880 --> 00:08:41.040
The royal hunt readies to depart.

158
00:08:41.150 --> 00:08:44.020
I've decided to remain here

159
00:08:41.150 --> 00:08:44.020
and read instead.

160
00:08:45.120 --> 00:08:45.990
[Samwell singing]

161
00:08:46.050 --> 00:08:47.490
You may go. Samwell.

162
00:08:48.220 --> 00:08:50.620
You are to stay

163
00:08:48.220 --> 00:08:50.620
by order of the Princess.

164
00:08:51.330 --> 00:08:54.490
The Queen commands you

165
00:08:51.330 --> 00:08:54.490
to leave the Godswood at once.

166
00:08:56.900 --> 00:08:58.130
Princess.

167
00:08:59.570 --> 00:09:00.400
[sighs]

168
00:09:01.240 --> 00:09:02.330
[Samwell] Your Grace.

169
00:09:06.040 --> 00:09:07.810
[Alicent] The King wishes

170
00:09:06.040 --> 00:09:07.810
for you to join us.

171
00:09:07.880 --> 00:09:10.680
The King has much to celebrate.

172
00:09:07.880 --> 00:09:10.680
He does not need me.

173
00:09:10.750 --> 00:09:12.210
[Alicent] He wants for us all

174
00:09:10.750 --> 00:09:12.210
to be together.

175
00:09:13.380 --> 00:09:16.370
Perhaps the hunt could be... fun.

176
00:09:17.550 --> 00:09:19.320
Is it the King's command?

177
00:09:20.360 --> 00:09:22.550
- Yes. but it--

178
00:09:20.360 --> 00:09:22.550
- Then at once. Your Grace.

179
00:09:23.490 --> 00:09:24.690
[Alicent] But it needn't be.

180
00:09:25.660 --> 00:09:29.060
None of it needs be this way

181
00:09:25.660 --> 00:09:29.060
in truth. Rhaenyra.

182
00:09:32.000 --> 00:09:32.870
[hooves thudding]

183
00:09:37.870 --> 00:09:39.840
[Viserys I] Well. isn't this splendid?

184
00:09:40.280 --> 00:09:42.270
The whole of our family

185
00:09:40.280 --> 00:09:42.270
off to celebration

186
00:09:42.380 --> 00:09:44.280
and adventure in the Kingswood.

187
00:09:46.880 --> 00:09:48.280
[rumbling]

188
00:09:49.850 --> 00:09:51.010
[Aegon Il babbling]

189
00:09:51.090 --> 00:09:53.110
Should you be traveling

190
00:09:51.090 --> 00:09:53.110
in such condition?

191
00:09:53.220 --> 00:09:56.020
The maester said that being out

192
00:09:53.220 --> 00:09:56.020
in nature would do me well.

193
00:09:56.520 --> 00:09:59.720
Well. you will be with your own child

194
00:09:56.520 --> 00:09:59.720
sooner than late.

195
00:09:59.790 --> 00:10:01.850
and make me a proud grandsire.

196
00:10:03.530 --> 00:10:05.590
It's not so bad.

197
00:10:05.700 --> 00:10:09.100
The days are long. but Aegon

198
00:10:05.700 --> 00:10:09.100
came quickly and without fuss.

199
00:10:17.050 --> 00:10:19.240
You should ride out with me today.

200
00:10:20.220 --> 00:10:21.270
Join in the chase.

201
00:10:22.150 --> 00:10:23.380
I'd rather not.

202
00:10:24.120 --> 00:10:27.280
The boars squeal like children

203
00:10:24.120 --> 00:10:27.280
when they're being slaughtered.

204
00:10:27.390 --> 00:10:29.650
I find it discomforting.

205
00:10:29.760 --> 00:10:31.420
It's a hunt. Rhaenyra.

206
00:10:32.330 --> 00:10:33.260
[Aegon Il yells]

207
00:10:34.060 --> 00:10:36.790
[Viserys I] How would you

208
00:10:34.060 --> 00:10:36.790
like to participate?

209
00:10:36.900 --> 00:10:38.160
I'm not sure why I must.

210
00:10:38.270 --> 00:10:40.330
Because you are my daughter...

211
00:10:40.440 --> 00:10:41.490
The Princess.

212
00:10:42.570 --> 00:10:44.230
And you have duties.

213
00:10:44.310 --> 00:10:46.300
As I am ceaselessly reminded.

214
00:10:46.410 --> 00:10:48.670
- [Viserys I] I'm sorry?

215
00:10:46.410 --> 00:10:48.670
- As I am ceaselessly reminded.

216
00:10:48.780 --> 00:10:51.970
You wouldn't need to be reminded

217
00:10:48.780 --> 00:10:51.970
if you ever attended to them.

218
00:10:52.080 --> 00:10:54.070
No one's here for me.

219
00:11:00.960 --> 00:11:02.180
[music playing]

220
00:11:02.290 --> 00:11:04.780
[indistinct chatter]

221
00:11:16.300 --> 00:11:19.870
[people cheering]

222
00:11:56.040 --> 00:11:59.070
Hail. hail Aegon. the Conqueror-Babe.

223
00:11:56.040 --> 00:11:59.070
Second of His Name!

224
00:12:00.180 --> 00:12:02.910
Here's to His Grace

225
00:12:00.180 --> 00:12:02.910
on his second name day!

226
00:12:12.330 --> 00:12:14.090
[indistinct chatter]

227
00:12:49.430 --> 00:12:52.400
[woman] Lady Johanna was reported

228
00:12:49.430 --> 00:12:52.400
to have been abducted

229
00:12:52.470 --> 00:12:55.600
when one of Lord Swann's ships

230
00:12:52.470 --> 00:12:55.600
sailed through the Stepstones.

231
00:12:55.700 --> 00:12:57.400
What will happen to Lady Johanna?

232
00:12:57.470 --> 00:13:00.310
She's to be sold to a pillow house

233
00:12:57.470 --> 00:13:00.310
in the Free Cities

234
00:13:00.410 --> 00:13:02.400
if you believe the rumors.

235
00:13:03.880 --> 00:13:06.470
I fear the gods did not

236
00:13:03.880 --> 00:13:06.470
make me for hunting.

237
00:13:06.580 --> 00:13:07.980
Might I sit with you. my ladies?

238
00:13:08.080 --> 00:13:09.880
[Alicent] But of course. Please join us.

239
00:13:10.750 --> 00:13:14.250
Larys Strong. the youngest son of our

240
00:13:10.750 --> 00:13:14.250
Master of Law. Lord Lyonel.

241
00:13:14.320 --> 00:13:15.880
My lord husband says that no king

242
00:13:15.960 --> 00:13:18.550
has even been able to tame

243
00:13:15.960 --> 00:13:18.550
the Stepstones for long.

244
00:13:18.630 --> 00:13:21.650
It's an inhospitable place

245
00:13:18.630 --> 00:13:21.650
suited only for savages.

246
00:13:21.760 --> 00:13:25.390
Perhaps the Princess...

247
00:13:21.760 --> 00:13:25.390
can give us some insight.

248
00:13:26.170 --> 00:13:29.970
[chuckles] Oh. I'm not sure how I could.

249
00:13:26.170 --> 00:13:29.970
I've never been to the Stepstones.

250
00:13:30.070 --> 00:13:33.060
Your dear uncle is the great mind

251
00:13:30.070 --> 00:13:33.060
behind this war.

252
00:13:33.140 --> 00:13:35.010
- Is he not?

253
00:13:33.140 --> 00:13:35.010
- I wouldn't know.

254
00:13:35.110 --> 00:13:36.510
I've not spoken to Daemon in years.

255
00:13:36.610 --> 00:13:38.510
Since you supplanted him as heir.

256
00:13:38.610 --> 00:13:40.780
Daemon made his choices. Lady Ceira.

257
00:13:41.450 --> 00:13:43.150
The Princess was more suited

258
00:13:41.450 --> 00:13:43.150
to the role.

259
00:13:44.320 --> 00:13:47.310
[Ceira] He's made a mess

260
00:13:44.320 --> 00:13:47.310
and the King must put an end to it.

261
00:13:47.420 --> 00:13:51.590
Send fleets and men

262
00:13:47.420 --> 00:13:51.590
and clear out the Triarchy for good.

263
00:13:52.790 --> 00:13:54.420
But the Crown is not at war.

264
00:13:55.160 --> 00:13:58.260
The Crown... is at war. Princess.

265
00:13:58.330 --> 00:14:00.100
Though your father refuses to admit it.

266
00:14:00.170 --> 00:14:03.000
we've been dragged into it by your uncle

267
00:14:00.170 --> 00:14:03.000
and the Sea Snake.

268
00:14:03.100 --> 00:14:06.630
And how have you served the realm

269
00:14:03.100 --> 00:14:06.630
of late. Lady Redwyne. by eating cake?

270
00:14:11.950 --> 00:14:13.780
[music playing]

271
00:14:17.350 --> 00:14:18.880
[indistinct chatter]

272
00:14:39.740 --> 00:14:41.840
I wonder. Princess...

273
00:14:41.910 --> 00:14:44.540
was your own second name day

274
00:14:41.910 --> 00:14:44.540
as grand as this?

275
00:14:45.210 --> 00:14:48.050
I honestly don't recall

276
00:14:45.210 --> 00:14:48.050
and neither will Aegon.

277
00:14:50.690 --> 00:14:52.020
Lord Jason Lannister.

278
00:14:53.190 --> 00:14:55.420
I gathered that from all the lions.

279
00:14:55.520 --> 00:14:57.520
I don't think we've been

280
00:14:55.520 --> 00:14:57.520
properly introduced.

281
00:15:00.600 --> 00:15:03.590
Your twin serves on my father's council.

282
00:15:04.100 --> 00:15:06.530
Tyland is...

283
00:15:06.600 --> 00:15:09.830
frightfully dull. gods love him.

284
00:15:09.900 --> 00:15:11.700
The finest honeyed wine

285
00:15:09.900 --> 00:15:11.700
you'll ever taste.

