00:29:34.200 --> 00:29:37.190
Princess. I must make a final plea

573
00:29:34.200 --> 00:29:37.190
that we return to the camp.

574
00:29:37.270 --> 00:29:38.470
[crickets chirping]

575
00:29:38.570 --> 00:29:40.560
I rather prefer it here.

576
00:29:42.480 --> 00:29:45.710
His Grace is certain to be worried

577
00:29:42.480 --> 00:29:45.710
by your absence.

578
00:29:45.780 --> 00:29:49.770
His Grace can worry

579
00:29:45.780 --> 00:29:49.770
himself to death if he so likes.

580
00:30:00.090 --> 00:30:01.580
Tell me something. Ser Criston.

581
00:30:03.400 --> 00:30:06.390
Do you think the realm will

582
00:30:03.400 --> 00:30:06.390
ever accept me as their Queen?

583
00:30:14.070 --> 00:30:16.670
They'll have no choice but to. Princess.

584
00:30:19.650 --> 00:30:21.140
[horse whinnies]

585
00:30:32.930 --> 00:30:34.020
[twigs snapping]

586
00:30:40.030 --> 00:30:43.030
[braying]

587
00:30:59.290 --> 00:31:03.020
[breath trembling]

588
00:31:14.030 --> 00:31:15.700
- [intense music playing]

589
00:31:14.030 --> 00:31:15.700
- [snarling]

590
00:31:16.170 --> 00:31:17.360
[grunts]

591
00:31:20.310 --> 00:31:22.070
[growls]

592
00:31:22.810 --> 00:31:25.010
[grunting]

593
00:31:25.080 --> 00:31:26.050
[growling]

594
00:31:29.820 --> 00:31:30.840
[shrieks]

595
00:31:31.750 --> 00:31:33.190
[Criston grunts]

596
00:31:33.250 --> 00:31:35.550
[both panting]

597
00:31:41.030 --> 00:31:43.160
- [snarling]

598
00:31:41.030 --> 00:31:43.160
- [grunting]

599
00:31:43.230 --> 00:31:44.530
[boar shrieking]

600
00:31:48.840 --> 00:31:52.400
[sobbing]

601
00:32:12.730 --> 00:32:14.720
Is everything all right. Your Grace?

602
00:32:17.200 --> 00:32:18.430
[sighs]

603
00:32:18.530 --> 00:32:19.900
You know. I...

604
00:32:20.900 --> 00:32:25.100
I named her to protect

605
00:32:20.900 --> 00:32:25.100
the realm from Daemon.

606
00:32:27.740 --> 00:32:29.570
She was my only child.

607
00:32:31.080 --> 00:32:33.070
"The Realm's Delight."

608
00:32:33.980 --> 00:32:35.970
I named her out of love

609
00:32:37.120 --> 00:32:39.280
because I no longer believed...

610
00:32:40.820 --> 00:32:42.450
Believed what. my love?

611
00:32:43.120 --> 00:32:44.250
[sighs]

612
00:32:50.900 --> 00:32:53.890
Many in my line have been dragonriders.

613
00:32:55.970 --> 00:32:58.340
Very few among us have been dreamers.

614
00:33:02.840 --> 00:33:05.340
What is the power of a dragon...

615
00:33:05.450 --> 00:33:07.410
next to the power of prophecy?

616
00:33:07.480 --> 00:33:08.950
The hour is too late. husband.

617
00:33:09.020 --> 00:33:11.110
When Rhaenyra was a child...

618
00:33:11.180 --> 00:33:12.020
[somber music playing]

619
00:33:12.120 --> 00:33:14.110
I saw it in a dream...

620
00:33:15.290 --> 00:33:17.690
as vivid as these flames. I saw it.

621
00:33:19.460 --> 00:33:23.020
A male babe born to me...

622
00:33:23.130 --> 00:33:25.120
wearing the Conqueror's crown.

623
00:33:27.470 --> 00:33:29.940
And I so wanted it to be true.

624
00:33:30.000 --> 00:33:32.200
to be a dreamer myself.

625
00:33:34.440 --> 00:33:37.430
I sought that vision again.

626
00:33:34.440 --> 00:33:37.430
night after night...

627
00:33:38.810 --> 00:33:40.800
but it never came again.

628
00:33:42.380 --> 00:33:45.480
I poured all my thought

629
00:33:42.380 --> 00:33:45.480
and will into it.

630
00:33:47.990 --> 00:33:50.620
And my obsession

631
00:33:47.990 --> 00:33:50.620
killed Rhaenyra's mother.

632
00:33:50.690 --> 00:33:52.160
[Alicent] Viserys.

633
00:33:53.190 --> 00:33:58.190
[Viserys I] I thought Rhaenyra was the

634
00:33:53.190 --> 00:33:58.190
way out of my abyss of grief and regret.

635
00:34:00.170 --> 00:34:02.640
And naming her heir

636
00:34:00.170 --> 00:34:02.640
would begin to set things right.

637
00:34:02.700 --> 00:34:05.700
- Oh. it did.

638
00:34:02.700 --> 00:34:05.700
- I never imagined I would remarry...

639
00:34:06.640 --> 00:34:08.230
that I would have a son.

640
00:34:13.250 --> 00:34:15.240
What if I was wrong?

641
00:34:21.250 --> 00:34:25.850
[horn blows]

642
00:34:36.440 --> 00:34:37.870
[splashes]

643
00:34:42.680 --> 00:34:44.670
- [birds chirping]

644
00:34:42.680 --> 00:34:44.670
- [dogs barking]

645
00:35:14.980 --> 00:35:16.940
- [man 1 grunts]

646
00:35:14.980 --> 00:35:16.940
- [hart groaning]

647
00:35:17.040 --> 00:35:18.240
[man 2] Left.

648
00:35:19.050 --> 00:35:21.640
[groaning]

649
00:35:22.450 --> 00:35:24.710
[men grunting]

650
00:35:24.780 --> 00:35:26.550
[somber music playing]

651
00:35:26.620 --> 00:35:28.890
He may not be white. Your Grace.

652
00:35:28.960 --> 00:35:30.080
But he's a big lad.

653
00:35:30.720 --> 00:35:32.160
[dogs barking]

654
00:35:33.460 --> 00:35:35.120
[horse whinnies]

655
00:35:37.100 --> 00:35:40.470
Your Grace... for the kill.

656
00:35:52.280 --> 00:35:55.310
[hart groaning]

657
00:35:55.420 --> 00:35:56.910
[dog barking]

658
00:35:56.980 --> 00:35:59.450
[huffing]

659
00:35:59.520 --> 00:36:00.750
[groaning]

660
00:36:06.130 --> 00:36:07.750
Right here. Your Grace.

661
00:36:09.500 --> 00:36:10.990
[hart groaning]

662
00:36:14.430 --> 00:36:15.530
[grunts]

663
00:36:17.370 --> 00:36:18.340
[yells]

664
00:36:18.440 --> 00:36:20.840
[hart wailing]

665
00:36:32.520 --> 00:36:34.510
[barking]

666
00:36:34.620 --> 00:36:36.180
[hart wailing]

667
00:36:38.160 --> 00:36:41.150
One more time. Your Grace.

668
00:36:38.160 --> 00:36:41.150
A little bit to your left.

669
00:36:43.130 --> 00:36:44.530
[hart groaning]

670
00:36:52.910 --> 00:36:54.970
- [yells]

671
00:36:52.910 --> 00:36:54.970
- [hart wails]

672
00:36:55.980 --> 00:37:01.350
[wailing]

673
00:37:01.410 --> 00:37:04.350
[breathing heavily]

674
00:37:08.050 --> 00:37:09.040
[grunts]

675
00:37:16.230 --> 00:37:18.720
[all applauding]

676
00:37:25.000 --> 00:37:27.240
[wind blowing]

677
00:37:41.450 --> 00:37:43.450
[hart huffing]

678
00:38:01.780 --> 00:38:03.440
[groans]

679
00:38:05.910 --> 00:38:07.780
[music playing]

680
00:38:07.880 --> 00:38:08.910
[brays]

681
00:38:12.620 --> 00:38:14.050
[whispers] No.

682
00:38:14.120 --> 00:38:17.110
[hart huffing]

683
00:38:34.440 --> 00:38:37.600
[music playing]

684
00:38:37.680 --> 00:38:39.510
[indistinct chatter]

685
00:39:32.900 --> 00:39:36.890
[baby crying]

686
00:39:37.000 --> 00:39:38.300
Come. sweet Prince.

687
00:39:38.370 --> 00:39:40.530
Let's give Her Grace some peace.

688
00:39:55.490 --> 00:39:57.320
Did you enjoy the hunt. Your Grace?

689
00:39:58.490 --> 00:40:01.930
- Well enough.

690
00:39:58.490 --> 00:40:01.930
- How fared my grandson?

691
00:40:03.060 --> 00:40:05.660
The ladies Lannister and Redwyne

692
00:40:03.060 --> 00:40:05.660
were quite taken with him.

693
00:40:05.730 --> 00:40:07.720
[Otto] As they should be.

694
00:40:08.670 --> 00:40:10.660
He's the future of the realm.

695
00:40:12.240 --> 00:40:15.230
You yourself witnessed

696
00:40:12.240 --> 00:40:15.230
the scale of the celebration.

697
00:40:15.340 --> 00:40:17.570
how it's united the men.

698
00:40:17.680 --> 00:40:19.080
When you bore the King a son.

699
00:40:19.180 --> 00:40:22.380
you ended 15 years

700
00:40:19.180 --> 00:40:22.380
of uncertainty and doubt.

701
00:40:23.380 --> 00:40:24.780
Aegon. like his namesake.

702
00:40:24.880 --> 00:40:27.290
was born to rule the Seven Kingdoms.

703
00:40:28.220 --> 00:40:32.220
If Viserys were to name him heir.

704
00:40:28.220 --> 00:40:32.220
the realm would fete him for it.

705
00:40:37.800 --> 00:40:39.430
And does this not please you?

706
00:40:39.900 --> 00:40:43.530
- Do you not want your son to be King?

707
00:40:39.900 --> 00:40:43.530
- And what mother wouldn't?

708
00:40:44.640 --> 00:40:46.610
[Otto] You mustn't ignore

709
00:40:44.640 --> 00:40:46.610
the certain truth

710
00:40:46.710 --> 00:40:49.800
that if Rhaenyra were to step over Aegon

711
00:40:46.710 --> 00:40:49.800
to ascend the throne.

712
00:40:49.910 --> 00:40:52.240
the realm would tear itself apart.

713
00:40:54.210 --> 00:40:57.410
They all swore obeisance to her.

714
00:40:54.210 --> 00:40:57.410
our house among them.

715
00:40:57.480 --> 00:40:59.480
[Otto] That was before Aegon.

716
00:41:00.820 --> 00:41:02.250
Rhaenyra will be a good queen.

717
00:41:02.320 --> 00:41:06.760
It wouldn't matter if she were

718
00:41:02.320 --> 00:41:06.760
Jaehaerys himself born again.

719
00:41:08.730 --> 00:41:11.630
- Rhaenyra is a woman.

720
00:41:08.730 --> 00:41:11.630
- [Alicent] What of my son?

721
00:41:11.730 --> 00:41:14.630
Would you have me raise a man

722
00:41:11.730 --> 00:41:14.630
to steal his own sister's birthright?

723
00:41:14.730 --> 00:41:17.640
[Otto] It is Aegon that's being robbed.

724
00:41:17.740 --> 00:41:19.670
He's the firstborn son of the King.

725
00:41:19.770 --> 00:41:21.830
To deny that he is heir to the throne

726
00:41:21.940 --> 00:41:24.310
is to assail the laws of gods and men.

727
00:41:26.510 --> 00:41:30.470
The road ahead is uncertain.

728
00:41:26.510 --> 00:41:30.470
but the end is clear.

729
00:41:30.580 --> 00:41:32.580
Aegon will be king.

730
00:41:34.320 --> 00:41:36.950
You must guide Viserys towards reason.

731
00:41:39.760 --> 00:41:41.750
He'll never find it on his own.

732
00:41:41.830 --> 00:41:43.520
[Viserys I breathing heavily]

733
00:41:49.670 --> 00:41:51.260
[Alicent] How are you feeling. husband?

734
00:41:51.340 --> 00:41:54.310
The gods have punished me

735
00:41:51.340 --> 00:41:54.310
for my indulgences.

736
00:41:54.370 --> 00:41:56.540
- [door closes]

737
00:41:54.370 --> 00:41:56.540
- At least the wine was good.

738
00:41:56.640 --> 00:41:57.940
- [sighs] Too good.

739
00:41:56.640 --> 00:41:57.940
- [Alicent chuckles]

740
00:42:01.150 --> 00:42:02.340
[Viserys I sighs]

741
00:42:10.290 --> 00:42:12.350
I was hoping we might discuss something.

742
00:42:13.530 --> 00:42:14.490
[sighs]

743
00:42:15.500 --> 00:42:16.690
Rhaenyra?

744
00:42:18.970 --> 00:42:19.830
[sighs]

745
00:42:20.800 --> 00:42:23.200
I do not think she enjoyed

746
00:42:20.800 --> 00:42:23.200
Jason Lannister's company.

747
00:42:24.540 --> 00:42:26.730
She is cross.

748
00:42:26.840 --> 00:42:28.710
I warned you that she would be.

749
00:42:28.810 --> 00:42:30.740
Rhaenyra has come of age.

750
00:42:30.840 --> 00:42:33.680
She must needs marry a high lord

751
00:42:30.840 --> 00:42:33.680
who will honor her. defend her.

752
00:42:33.750 --> 00:42:35.510
and serve her as king consort.

753
00:42:36.220 --> 00:42:39.010
Her wishes in this matter

754
00:42:36.220 --> 00:42:39.010
are irrelevant.

755
00:42:39.090 --> 00:42:42.080
I do believe that Rhaenyra

756
00:42:39.090 --> 00:42:42.080
will marry. Your Grace.

757
00:42:42.860 --> 00:42:45.880
But she must believe

758
00:42:42.860 --> 00:42:45.880
it is her choice to do so.

759
00:42:52.230 --> 00:42:53.430
[grunts]

760
00:42:54.570 --> 00:42:57.000
- What's this?

761
00:42:54.570 --> 00:42:57.000
- [Viserys I] A letter...

762
00:42:57.070 --> 00:42:58.370
[thuds]

763
00:42:59.040 --> 00:43:01.030
...from Vaemond Velaryon.

764
00:43:01.510 --> 00:43:04.100
- [Alicent] The Sea Snake's brother?

765
00:43:01.510 --> 00:43:04.100
- Yeah.

766
00:43:04.940 --> 00:43:07.380
He's fighting in the Stepstones.

767
00:43:07.450 --> 00:43:09.080
with all the rest of them.

768
00:43:14.390 --> 00:43:15.450
May I?

769
00:43:26.530 --> 00:43:29.130
Lord Corlys and Prince Daemon

770
00:43:26.530 --> 00:43:29.130
are losing their war.

771
00:43:29.770 --> 00:43:31.970
Badly. by all accounts.

772
00:43:32.740 --> 00:43:34.600
This is a plea for aid.

773
00:43:37.140 --> 00:43:39.140
Then why not send it?

774
00:43:39.250 --> 00:43:42.310
[Viserys I] Because it is a war

775
00:43:39.250 --> 00:43:42.310
started by two malcontents.

776
00:43:42.420 --> 00:43:44.610
unhappy with decisions I made.

777
00:43:46.090 --> 00:43:49.250
If I now provide

778
00:43:46.090 --> 00:43:49.250
Daemon and Corlys succor.

779
00:43:49.320 --> 00:43:50.790
what will that say of their King?

780
00:43:50.890 --> 00:43:53.590
Perhaps. that he is a good man who

781
00:43:50.890 --> 00:43:53.590
loves his brother.

782
00:43:53.660 --> 00:43:56.960
Well. if you truly

783
00:43:53.660 --> 00:43:56.960
believe that. my dear...

784
00:43:57.060 --> 00:43:59.260
then you possess a generous spirit.

785
00:44:00.770 --> 00:44:03.100
What do you believe. Viserys?

786
00:44:06.440 --> 00:44:08.600
That I am forever doomed

787
00:44:06.440 --> 00:44:08.600
to anger one person

788
00:44:08.670 --> 00:44:10.300
in the pleasing of another.

789
00:44:11.010 --> 00:44:13.000
[Alicent] Then I pose

790
00:44:11.010 --> 00:44:13.000
a simpler question.

791
00:44:14.110 --> 00:44:17.140
Is it better for the realm

792
00:44:14.110 --> 00:44:17.140
if the Crabfeeder thrives.

793
00:44:17.250 --> 00:44:18.840
or is vanquished?

794
00:44:22.320 --> 00:44:23.520
[door opens]

795
00:44:25.630 --> 00:44:27.620
[Viserys I] Make haste to Dwarfstone.

796
00:44:25.630 --> 00:44:27.620
Ser Addam.

797
00:44:27.690 --> 00:44:30.030
Hand-deliver this

798
00:44:27.690 --> 00:44:30.030
to Prince Daemon yourself.

799
00:44:30.130 --> 00:44:31.690
At once. Your Grace.

800
00:44:40.210 --> 00:44:43.640
- Dwarfstone?

801
00:44:40.210 --> 00:44:43.640
- I'm sending word to Daemon.

802
00:44:43.710 --> 00:44:46.140
Aid is sailing to the Stepstones.

803
00:44:46.210 --> 00:44:47.040
[door closes]

804
00:44:47.150 --> 00:44:50.980
- Did he make call for help?

805
00:44:47.150 --> 00:44:50.980
- He would sooner die.

806
00:44:51.050 --> 00:44:53.280
But his king does not mean

807
00:44:51.050 --> 00:44:53.280
to allow that.

808
00:44:57.890 --> 00:45:00.120
Do you not think my decision correct?

809
00:45:00.190 --> 00:45:02.690
It is no consequence to what I think...

810
00:45:02.800 --> 00:45:04.660
as I'm often reminded.

811
00:45:04.730 --> 00:45:05.720
[sighs]

812
00:45:05.830 --> 00:45:07.060
[chuckles]

813
00:45:07.170 --> 00:45:09.800
Daemon is thorn enough in my flesh.

814
00:45:10.540 --> 00:45:12.400
Will you insist on taking after him?

815
00:45:13.840 --> 00:45:15.500
Must everything be a battle?

816
00:45:15.580 --> 00:45:18.880
If you refer to your attempt

817
00:45:15.580 --> 00:45:18.880
to marry me off to Casterly Rock...

818
00:45:20.510 --> 00:45:21.910
I am sorry. Rhaenyra.

819
00:45:23.150 --> 00:45:26.680
I was trying to help you.

820
00:45:23.150 --> 00:45:26.680
Will you not be helped?

821
00:45:27.890 --> 00:45:31.260
Why must every effort

822
00:45:27.890 --> 00:45:31.260
on your behalf be resisted

823
00:45:31.360 --> 00:45:34.260
- as if to the death?

824
00:45:31.360 --> 00:45:34.260
- Because you mean to replace me...

825
00:45:35.190 --> 00:45:37.490
with Alicent Hightower's son.

826
00:45:37.560 --> 00:45:40.030
the boy you always wanted.

827
00:45:40.770 --> 00:45:42.330
You have him in hands now.

828
00:45:42.400 --> 00:45:44.930
You have no further use for me.

829
00:45:45.040 --> 00:45:47.340
You might as well peddle me

830
00:45:45.040 --> 00:45:47.340
for what you can.

831
00:45:47.410 --> 00:45:50.930
A mountain stronghold

832
00:45:47.410 --> 00:45:50.930
or a fleet of ships.

833
00:45:51.040 --> 00:45:53.070
You have misjudged me. Rhaenyra.

834
00:45:53.180 --> 00:45:54.940
All know it.

835
00:45:55.050 --> 00:45:57.110
Jason Lannister knows it.

836
00:45:57.220 --> 00:45:58.710
You said it yourself.

837
00:45:58.780 --> 00:46:01.620
the lords of the realm

838
00:45:58.780 --> 00:46:01.620
gather like vultures to a carcass.

839
00:46:01.720 --> 00:46:03.710
hoping to feast on my bones.

840
00:46:06.260 --> 00:46:10.390
It is true that as rulers

841
00:46:06.260 --> 00:46:10.390
we must marry for advantage

842
00:46:10.460 --> 00:46:13.560
to forge alliances

843
00:46:10.460 --> 00:46:13.560
and bolster our strength.

844
00:46:13.630 --> 00:46:16.100
You have always understood this.

845
00:46:16.770 --> 00:46:19.200
I myself was promised

846
00:46:16.770 --> 00:46:19.200
to your mother when I was--

847
00:46:19.270 --> 00:46:21.210
Ten-and-seven years of age.

848
00:46:21.270 --> 00:46:23.110
The Vale had an army to rival the North.

849
00:46:23.210 --> 00:46:25.740
I've heard that story

850
00:46:23.210 --> 00:46:25.740
since I've had ears to.

851
00:46:26.950 --> 00:46:28.940
I loved her.

852
00:46:29.580 --> 00:46:30.980
She made a man of me.

853
00:46:34.590 --> 00:46:36.950
I do not seek to replace you. child.

854
00:46:38.590 --> 00:46:40.820
You've been much alone

855
00:46:38.590 --> 00:46:40.820
these last few years.

856
00:46:40.930 --> 00:46:42.920
Alone and angry.

857
00:46:44.430 --> 00:46:46.130
I will not live forever.

858
00:46:46.230 --> 00:46:48.220
I wish to see you contented.

859
00:46:48.300 --> 00:46:49.790
happy even.

860
00:46:49.900 --> 00:46:51.170
You think a man will do it?

861
00:46:51.270 --> 00:46:53.260
- A family.

862
00:46:51.270 --> 00:46:53.260
- I had a family.

863
00:46:53.340 --> 00:46:54.900
What would you have me do?

864
00:46:54.970 --> 00:46:57.970
If it was for advantage.

865
00:46:54.970 --> 00:46:57.970
you would've wed Laena Velaryon!

866
00:47:02.920 --> 00:47:04.510
That is true enough.

867
00:47:07.190 --> 00:47:09.310
You must marry.

868
00:47:10.020 --> 00:47:12.650
strengthen your own claim.

869
00:47:12.760 --> 00:47:14.950
shore up your succession.

870
00:47:15.030 --> 00:47:16.460
multiply.

871
00:47:17.860 --> 00:47:19.590
As to your match...

872
00:47:21.300 --> 00:47:22.670
make it yourself.

873
00:47:23.770 --> 00:47:25.500
Search him out.

874
00:47:25.600 --> 00:47:29.170
Find one that pleases you. as I did.

875
00:47:44.720 --> 00:47:45.950
Rhaenyra...

876
00:47:51.960 --> 00:47:54.700
I did waver at one time.

877
00:47:56.400 --> 00:47:59.840
But I swear to you now.

878
00:47:56.400 --> 00:47:59.840
on your mother's memory.

879
00:48:00.910 --> 00:48:02.400
you will not be supplanted.

880
00:48:11.880 --> 00:48:12.980
[door opens]

881
00:48:16.520 --> 00:48:18.720
[ominous music playing]

882
00:48:28.730 --> 00:48:30.760
[dragon growls]

883
00:48:46.450 --> 00:48:49.720
[Corlys] We have 16. perhaps 18.

884
00:48:46.450 --> 00:48:49.720
seaworthy ships.

885
00:48:49.790 --> 00:48:52.050
Seven hundred foot. some 60 knights.

886
00:48:52.120 --> 00:48:55.890
Our food quickly dwindles.

887
00:48:52.120 --> 00:48:55.890
save for what we can fish from the sea.

888
00:48:55.960 --> 00:48:57.290
I would say we have a fortnight.

889
00:48:57.400 --> 00:49:00.090
mayhaps a bit longer

890
00:48:57.400 --> 00:49:00.090
with strict rationing.

891
00:49:00.200 --> 00:49:02.190
I've made call for Driftmark

892
00:49:00.200 --> 00:49:02.190
to send more ships.

893
00:49:02.270 --> 00:49:04.860
but they will be weeks away.

894
00:49:04.940 --> 00:49:07.430
We are faltering

895
00:49:04.940 --> 00:49:07.430
and the Triarchy knows it.

896
00:49:07.540 --> 00:49:11.100
We must press the attack.

897
00:49:07.540 --> 00:49:11.100
continue sending the dragons.

898
00:49:11.210 --> 00:49:12.470
[Laenor] It's pointless. Father.

899
00:49:13.550 --> 00:49:16.310
The Crabfeeder has

900
00:49:13.550 --> 00:49:16.310
created a chokepoint here.

901
00:49:16.420 --> 00:49:18.080
beyond these dunes.

902
00:49:18.580 --> 00:49:19.950
Archers hold the high positions.

903
00:49:20.050 --> 00:49:21.710
foot soldiers hold the ground.

904
00:49:21.790 --> 00:49:23.950
We've strafed them on

905
00:49:21.790 --> 00:49:23.950
dragonback again and again.

906
00:49:24.060 --> 00:49:26.320
but they just retreat within the caves.

907
00:49:26.430 --> 00:49:30.160
Dragons can circle Bloodstone

908
00:49:26.430 --> 00:49:30.160
until they fall out of the sky.

909
00:49:30.260 --> 00:49:33.290
The Crabfeeder and his men

910
00:49:30.260 --> 00:49:33.290
have no reason to leave those caves.

911
00:49:33.770 --> 00:49:35.230
[Laenor] We must give them one.

912
00:49:35.300 --> 00:49:38.170
an offering of flesh to bait the crab.

913
00:49:38.270 --> 00:49:39.830
Who?

914
00:49:39.940 --> 00:49:41.770
[man] Dragon returning!

915
00:49:41.840 --> 00:49:43.140
[whinnying]

916
00:49:49.010 --> 00:49:50.510
[Vaemond] Yes. Who?

917
00:49:50.620 --> 00:49:53.020
Which man here

918
00:49:50.620 --> 00:49:53.020
will happily go to his death?

919
00:49:53.120 --> 00:49:55.110
Show me the knight

920
00:49:53.120 --> 00:49:55.110
who will march into that hell pit.

921
00:49:55.190 --> 00:49:56.920
nephew. and I will show you a madman.

922
00:49:56.990 --> 00:49:59.820
- Daemon.

923
00:49:56.990 --> 00:49:59.820
- Daemon is why we are losing!

924
00:49:59.930 --> 00:50:02.330
[Laenor] He at least

925
00:49:59.930 --> 00:50:02.330
is fighting this war.

926
00:50:02.430 --> 00:50:05.090
What role have you played

927
00:50:02.430 --> 00:50:05.090
in his council. Uncle.

928
00:50:05.160 --> 00:50:06.930
- other than Master of Complaints?

929
00:50:05.160 --> 00:50:06.930
- Enough. Laenor.

930
00:50:07.000 --> 00:50:09.990
[Vaemond] If King's Landing

931
00:50:07.000 --> 00:50:09.990
will not support Daemon.

932
00:50:10.100 --> 00:50:11.760
why should any of us?

933
00:50:17.980 --> 00:50:21.970
Blood or no. Vaemond.

934
00:50:17.980 --> 00:50:21.970
I will not have you stoke mutiny.

935
00:50:43.540 --> 00:50:45.970
If you do not seize control

936
00:50:43.540 --> 00:50:45.970
of this war. my lord.

937
00:50:46.040 --> 00:50:48.470
the crabs will soon dine on all of us.

938
00:51:04.890 --> 00:51:06.260
Prince Daemon.

939
00:51:06.360 --> 00:51:09.160
I bring word from His Grace.

940
00:51:06.360 --> 00:51:09.160
Viserys Targaryen.

941
00:51:09.230 --> 00:51:10.990
first of his name. King of the Andals.

942
00:51:11.060 --> 00:51:12.930
the Rhoynar. and the First Men.

943
00:51:13.030 --> 00:51:16.030
Lord of the Seven Kingdoms.

944
00:51:13.030 --> 00:51:16.030
and Protector of the Realm.

945
00:51:33.950 --> 00:51:35.580
[somber music playing]

946
00:51:52.470 --> 00:51:54.240
[muffled grunting]

947
00:51:58.810 --> 00:52:02.410
That's enough! Stop!

948
00:52:03.750 --> 00:52:05.150
[indistinct shouting]

949
00:52:17.630 --> 00:52:18.760
[Viserys I] Brother...

950
00:52:19.670 --> 00:52:24.130
I have ordered 10 ships and 2.000 men

951
00:52:19.670 --> 00:52:24.130
to set sail from King's Landing

952
00:52:24.240 --> 00:52:26.640
to join the effort in the Stepstones.

953
00:52:28.070 --> 00:52:31.510
Though time and circumstance

954
00:52:28.070 --> 00:52:31.510
have seen us estranged.

955
00:52:31.610 --> 00:52:36.240
know that it is not my desire to see you

956
00:52:31.610 --> 00:52:36.240
fail in your cause.

957
00:52:36.320 --> 00:52:38.780
It is instead my hope

958
00:52:36.320 --> 00:52:38.780
that this aid will deliver

959
00:52:38.850 --> 00:52:41.650
the victory that has thus far evaded us.

960
00:52:43.920 --> 00:52:47.520
I shall pray nightly to

961
00:52:43.920 --> 00:52:47.520
the gods for your safe return.

962
